dataIdInfo.idPurp: This layer contains an easy-to-use input dataset for allocating the baseline nutrient loads and subsequent load reductions to meet the newly accepted TMDLs. This baseload layer summarizes the normalized outputs of a custom spatial-scale run of the Spatial Watershed Iterative Loading (SWIL) Model 4.0 to allow baseload allocation for stakeholders within the Banana River, North IRL, and Central IRL BMAPs. This layer contains period-of-record mean annual and dry season (January - May) raw volumes, TN, and TP loads corresponding to direct runoff, baseflow volumes and loads by catchment basin. The temporal extent was from 2004 to 2017. The spatial extent covered all areas within the Brevard County TMDL boundary.
dataIdInfo.idAbs: To produce the baseload catchment layer the loads in the Grid_Basin_v7_NormalizedValues layer were used. The Grid_Basin_v7_NormalizedValues layer contains load values per 50m by 50m grid cell over the entire area of interest. The Catchments_Water_Quality_Basins_v7 summarizes these loads by catchment basin.

dataLineage.statement:
The layer Catchments_Water_Quality_Basins_v7 was created based on two input layers: 1. Catchments_Hydrologic_Basins_v2 2. Grid_Basins_v7_NormalizedValues
An overview of the processing steps follows: 1. Remove basin areas outside of the TMDL boundary from Catchments_Hydrologic_Basins_v2 creating a new layer Catchments_Water_Quality_Basins 2. The single part to multipart tool was executed on the Catchments_Water_Quality_Basins. Any duplication in Catchment identifiers were resolved. 3. New basins were created in the layer Catchments_Water_Quality_Basins for areas within the area of interest not covered by the Catchments_Hydrologic_Basins_v2 layer. These basins were assigned Catchment identifiers SJR-1 to SJR-123. 4. The Union tool was executed on Catchments_Water_Quality_Basins and Grid_Basins_v7_NormalizedValues layers 5. Fields (18) were added for the load values 6. The Calculated Field tool was used to multiply the normalized loading values by the acres 7. The loads per catchment basin was summarized using the Summary Statistics tool 8. The output statistics table was joined to the Catchments_Water_Quality_Basins layer by Catchment ID
